                <head>192. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 16 elements of the Argentine Armed Forces launched a revolt against
                        <persName corresp="#p_PJD1">Perón</persName>. On September 19 <persName
                        corresp="#p_PJD1">Perón</persName> was forced to resign. He was replaced
                    that same day by a provisional military junta. Despatch 228 from Buenos Aires,
                    September 26, drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SEV1">Siracusa</persName> and
                    entitled “Peron Falls—The End of an Era,” summarized these developments.
                    (Department of State, Central Files, 735.00/9–2655) Additional documentation is
                        <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 735.00 and <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>,
                    Buenos Aires Embassy Files: Lot 64 F 71, 350, Revolt of Sept. 16, 1955.</p>
            </div>
